metadata.name: Ten
metadata.description:
A poem written and illustrated by Luke Dogwalker.
His genesis piece, serving also as the title piece to his collection available on OpenSea. 
"Ten" is a poem of self-discovery, realization, and celebration. With this piece, Luke celebrates his tenth year freed from addiction, as well as his first steps into web3.
Luke's work is lo-fi and accessible leading with the belief-
Poetry is the Utility.

"Ten"

it's taken ten years of waking
to walk this path
to circle
back to the beginning
and meet myself
where I am truly at

a dream

at last
I believe

I am an artist.

and this is no bold proclamation
but self actualization

no longer
sleepless
dreamless
monochrome sky

my eyes only behold stars
and everything is so bright
sober
and why else would I survive
but to learn to love
and trust
and paint full color words with this life
